et, they can sit their and cast away on you without fear of reprecussion.<br><br>Now I can understand the logic of having horses in the game. If people want to spend that much money on them or the AAXP points for them, more power to you, but to have an obvious bug in the game for this long and effectively null any chance of killing a horsed PC seems ridiculous. Try finishing off a SK or pally with a horse...They get low, click on their insta-horse, and puff, invulnerable.<br><br>I know that horsed PC's can still be melee'd. Yet for us who engage in solo PvP at times, or don't carry our &quot;Pocket Roag&quot; around, well we are SoL (and that's not Shadws of Luclin). Pet classes can still get by sometimes, yet still have their effectiveness reduced. But we being the pure damage spell casters are kinda taking it in the 2-hole in this matter. I've bugged this in game several times, had others as well, but it seems to be something either generally overlooked or not felt like it's that big of a deal.<br><br>Is this something that is just annoying to myself and the other wizards I talk to on my Server, or do other PvP servers have issues with this? I don't think any class should be untouchable by a certain class simply for the reason they've put a certain amount of AAXP's in or paid enough money. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaamdir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aamdir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/02 4:06:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=72.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.indignation.cc/forums/images/avatars/gallery/male1/00008.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP and the Horse Bug</span><hr size=1> yet another blatent problem with 